CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 3, 1965, pg. 4, reads: "'Dump and Junk' Area - This eyesore assails the eyes of any person willing to walk less than 60 feet from Centre Ave., any day. Lot-filled rubble, refuse of all kinds, along with the most unfortunate elements of a racially imprisoned society, live without hope - or complaint - week after week, year after year, in such surroundings.  Magistrate Harry B. Fitzgerald insists that 'We cannot expect to breed lilies in such cesspools.' - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Pile of garbage, broken furniture, junked car, and other debris, with men standing in street in background, near Centre Avenue, Hill District
